    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 14 June 1535)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Lucretia Caballis will tell him what they have heard
                            about the Turks. All of Syria, Egypt, and Greece is trembling with fear.
                            If it is true that the Emperor has defeated Hayreddin Barbarossa Pasha
                            and conquered Tunis, he will focus all his might on these locations.
                        </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/B3455EDF-14B1-40D6-8775-68959DA9E9E8
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao suo salutem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Quae a Turcis, <persName>Aenobarbo</persName><note xml:id="note.1"
                        >Hayreddin Barbarossa Pasha.</note> et caesaris classe habemus, de
                        <persName>Lucretia Virgine</persName><note xml:id="note.2">Lucretia Caballis
                        (vom Ross).</note> electissima intelliges, nos id audivimus
                        <placeName>Syriam</placeName>, <placeName>Aegiptum</placeName> et
                        <placeName>Graeciam</placeName> fere omnem tremere. Quod si verum est,
                    debellato <persName>Aenobarbo</persName> et capto
                        <placeName>Tuneto</placeName><note xml:id="note.3"
                        >Tunis.</note><persName>caesar</persName> vires suas in eas partes
                    convertet, et omnia in suam potestatem brevi redacturus est, quod postea
                    succedit, curabo, ut scias. Tu vero interea valebis et
                        <persName>Sceperum</persName><note xml:id="note.4">Cornelis de
                        Schepper.</note> nostrum et eius <persName>coniugem</persName><note
                        xml:id="note.5">Anna Isabella (Elizabeth) Donche.</note> meo nomine
                    salutabis. Iterum vale, Amicorum Optime. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> XIIII. Iunii MDXXXV.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
